        "content": "<p><code>Field R</code> can't be an instance because it creates data (the inverse and zpow etc.) If you start with a field, you then get two non-defeq Field instances on R. You can make it an abbrev though (similar to <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Quotient/Basic.html#Ideal.Quotient.field\">Ideal.Quotient.field</a>)</p>",
        "id": 495707704,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1737723298
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks, do you think it would be good to also have it? In the end it is one-liner:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">noncomputable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">abbrev</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">field_of_isReduced_of_isLocalRing</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">IsReduced</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">IsLocalRing</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Field</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">isField_of_isReduced_of_isLocalRing</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">toField</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>So maybe it does not pay off?</p>",
